1.subject: Mathematics
1.name: Sine Law
1.question: In \( \triangle ABC \), \( AB = 8 cm \), \( BC = 5 cm \), and \( \angle CAB = 20^\circ \). Find \( \angle ACB \) and \( AC \).

2.text:
\[
\begin{align*}
\text{By the sine law,}& \\
\frac{AC}{sin{126.823^\circ}} &\approx \frac{5 cm}{sin{20^\circ}} \\
AC &\approx \underline{\underline{11.7 cm}} \textit{(cor. to 1 d.p.)} \\
\end{align*}
\]

4.text:
\[
\begin{align*}
\text{By the sine law,}& \\
\frac{AC}{sin{13.177^\circ}} &\approx \frac{5 cm}{sin{20^\circ}} \\
AC &\approx \underline{\underline{3.3 cm}} \textit{(cor. to 1 d.p.)} \\
\end{align*}
\]

2.subject: Mathematics
2.name: Property of Geometric ratios
2.question: Given a geometric sequence \(T(n) = ar^n \), if \(T(2)=3 \) and \(T(4)=12\), find \(a\) and \(r\).

2.text:
\[
\begin{aligned}
\ [T(3)]^2 &= T(2) \times T(4) \\
T(3) &= \sqrt{3 \times 12} \\
T(3) &= \sqrt{36} \\
T(3) &= 6 \text{ or } T(3) = -6 \\
\end{aligned}
\]

3.text:
\[
\begin{aligned}
\text{For } T(3) &= 6 \text{, apply common ratio,} \\
r &= \frac{T(3)}{T(2)} \\
r &= \frac{6}{3} \\
r &= 2 \\
\end{aligned}
\]

5.text:
\[
\begin{aligned}
\text{For } T(3) &= -6 \text{, apply common ratio,} \\
r &= \frac{T(3)}{T(2)} \\
r &= \frac{-6}{3} \\
r &= -2 \\
\end{aligned}
\]
